description.narrative: The launch of the UNICEF supported Namibia Multidimensional Poverty Index (NaMPI) Report addressed existing data gaps for SDG (Goal 1) reporting and monitoring, whilst ensuring that both monetary and multidimensional child poverty is measured and reported by the government. The ensuing advocacy efforts resulted in the government committing to addressing child poverty in the sixth National Development Plan (NDP6). Evidence generated through the procurement analysis resulted in key policy reforms being instituted, by the government, in health procurement for improved efficiencies and thus outcomes for children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:01/12/2021
